CER — Character Error Rate
CER measures:
How many characters were wrong.
Formula:
CER=(S+D+I )/N

* S = Substitutions
* D = Deletions
* I = Insertions
* N = Total characters in actual text

WER — Word Error Rate

WER measures:
How many words were wrong.


CER=(S+D+I )/N
Same formula, but: N = total words

How CER/WER are Calculated Internally
They usually use:
* Levenshtein Distance
* Edit Distance Algorithm
This calculates:
* Minimum edits needed to convert prediction → actual text

Golden Dataset → Model Inference → Metric Calculation → Threshold Gate → CI/CD

def evaluate_model(preds, labels):
    precision = precision_score(labels, preds)
    recall = recall_score(labels, preds)
    f1 = f1_score(labels, preds)
    assert f1 >= 0.95

We treated model metrics as test assertions and blocked production promotion if any country/language slice regressed beyond defined error budgets.

